<i>You will always be</i>

34:28.366 --> 34:31.164
<i>You will always be</i>

34:31.235 --> 34:32.793
<i>My girl</i>

34:51.222 --> 34:53.018
You're working late.

34:55.326 --> 34:57.226
Someone has to, right?

35:05.169 --> 35:07.967
Mom, I know this has all
been really hard on you,

35:08.039 --> 35:10.701
but I just need you to trust me, okay?

35:11.309 --> 35:14.938
And no matter what happens,
I just wanted to tell you that

35:17.682 --> 35:21.311
I love you and I appreciate you

35:22.587 --> 35:25.920
and maybe I don't say that enough.

35:29.794 --> 35:32.786
Whatever. You can lock up.

35:35.032 --> 35:38.433
<i>You will always be my girl</i>

35:40.171 --> 35:42.833
<i>You will always be</i>

35:42.907 --> 35:44.465
<i>My girl</i>

36:06.531 --> 36:08.226
Saw your light on.

36:08.833 --> 36:12.667
Which isn't that surprising.
I mean, I know how hard you work.

36:14.839 --> 36:20.539
You know,
you haven't been yourself lately, Peyton.

36:21.145 --> 36:22.703
I mean, not the Peyton I remember.

36:22.780 --> 36:25.977
Well, I haven't been that Peyton
for three years.

36:27.118 --> 36:28.745
What's going on?

36:30.922 --> 36:32.048
Okay.

36:33.090 --> 36:35.024
I went by my old house.

36:35.893 --> 36:41.957
There's a teenage girl living there now
and she showed me my closet door.

36:42.333 --> 36:44.460
And you know what that said?

36:45.336 --> 36:48.203
"Lucas and Peyton. True Love Always."

36:49.540 --> 36:52.839
Always, Lucas.
That's what we were supposed to have

36:53.144 --> 36:57.672
until you showed up in LA
three years ago and ambushed me.

36:57.748 --> 37:00.182
If by "ambushed"
you mean "proposed" to you.

37:00.284 --> 37:02.650
Oh, yeah, out of the blue.

37:03.087 --> 37:06.614
A proposal that was driven by
some insecurity

37:06.691 --> 37:08.989
that I have never been able to understand.

37:09.060 --> 37:11.290
Insecurity? Right.

37:13.030 --> 37:15.931
Let me tell you
how you get "always," Peyton.

37:16.500 --> 37:18.900
When a man asks you to marry him,
you say, "Yes."

37:18.970 --> 37:21.131
You don't say, "No" and call him insecure.

37:21.205 --> 37:23.298
I never said, "No"!

37:24.342 --> 37:28.210
I said that I loved you and that I did
wanna marry you someday.

37:28.279 --> 37:31.771
And, oh, God, Luke, I wanted you so bad.

37:33.851 --> 37:36.411
- But you gave up on us.
- I gave up on us?

37:36.487 --> 37:38.819
- Yes!
- By proposing, I gave up on us?

37:38.889 --> 37:43.326
No, by not waiting you gave up on us
and you know that's the truth.

37:44.428 --> 37:46.225
That's great, Peyton.

37:46.464 --> 37:48.864
You wanna talk truth, let's tell the truth.

37:48.933 --> 37:52.164
- Okay.
- You gave up on me.

37:52.637 --> 37:56.232
That's why you didn't say, "Yes."
You didn't think I could do it.

37:56.307 --> 37:59.401
You didn't think
I could get my novel published.

37:59.543 --> 38:03.001
Maybe you just didn't care
because it wasn't about you,

38:03.681 --> 38:06.115
- or what you wanted.
- Well, if that's the truth,

38:06.183 --> 38:11.746
if I never cared, then how come
every time I see this stupid book I buy it?

38:11.822 --> 38:14.290
Every stupid damn time, Luke!

38:14.959 --> 38:18.725
You said I was great!
You said I could be great!

38:18.796 --> 38:20.889
You said we were destined to be together!

38:20.965 --> 38:23.024
You said it to the world, you said it to me,

38:23.100 --> 38:26.866
and I wish you never had
because you did not mean any of it.

38:27.738 --> 38:28.966
Oh, God.

38:30.441 --> 38:31.465
I'm gonna go.

38:31.542 --> 38:34.602
Okay, you know what? I wanna pay rent.
I don't know how I'm gonna do it,

38:34.679 --> 38:36.078
but I'll figure it out, I just...

38:36.147 --> 38:39.514
Whatever this is, I don't feel right about it.

38:41.852 --> 38:44.218
- It's called me being nice to you.
- Well, it needs to stop.

38:44.288 --> 38:46.813
You know, maybe you're right.

39:07.345 --> 39:11.941
<i>MAN: (SINGING)</i>
<i>It's looking like a limb torn off</i>

39:12.016 --> 39:17.648
<i>Or altogether just taken apart</i>

39:20.257 --> 39:24.785
<i>We're reeling through an endless fall</i>

39:24.862 --> 39:26.056
<i>We are...</i>

39:26.130 --> 39:27.495
Tough day.

39:28.366 --> 39:33.099
Sucks about Carlton, huh?
Well, you're lucky.

39:33.304 --> 39:37.741
At least Alice kind of likes you.
God help you if that ever goes south.

39:38.843 --> 39:40.310
Night, buddy.

39:44.081 --> 39:45.878
I'm gonna head home.

39:46.751 --> 39:49.276
By "home," I hope you mean my place.

39:50.721 --> 39:53.246
Actually, I'm not feeling very well.

39:55.760 --> 39:58.854
Then maybe you're not
on-air material after all.

40:00.097 --> 40:03.362
I mean, if you're gonna
start getting sick on me.

40:03.968 --> 40:08.905
I'm sure it's nothing. I'll get a good
night's rest and be back to normal.

40:09.473 --> 40:11.703
Yeah, yeah. I hope so.

40:13.778 --> 40:16.679
<i>But no one</i>

40:18.115 --> 40:22.882
<i>is ever gonna love you more than I do</i>

40:23.754 --> 40:24.982
(SIGHS)

40:25.756 --> 40:28.554
Millicent, I want you to reschedule
the meeting with Macy's.

40:28.626 --> 40:31.857
<i>- Your mom 's not gonna like that.</i>
- It's my company.

40:32.530 --> 40:35.556
And please do me a favor, call her
"Victoria," don't call her my mom.

40:35.633 --> 40:36.759
<i>Okay.</i>

40:36.834 --> 40:40.099
<i>If things start splitting at the seams</i>
<i>and now</i>

40:40.171 --> 40:42.901
<i>It's tumbling down</i>

40:42.973 --> 40:45.339
<i>Hard</i>

40:49.647 --> 40:51.137
<i>Anything to make...</i>

40:51.215 --> 40:54.878
Little man's out cold.
Do you need me to check for clowns?

40:54.952 --> 40:57.250
- I kind of do.
- All right.

40:59.890 --> 41:01.482
Good over there.

41:04.829 --> 41:06.763
All right, you're good.

41:07.398 --> 41:09.730
I think you forgot the balcony.

41:10.434 --> 41:11.628
Okay.

41:12.837 --> 41:14.134
I gotcha.

41:14.505 --> 41:17.338
<i>But no one</i>

41:18.809 --> 41:23.075
<i>is ever gonna love you more than I do</i>

41:25.249 --> 41:28.980
<i>No one's gonna love you more than I do</i>

41:30.354 --> 41:32.151
<i>But someone</i>

41:33.324 --> 41:36.122
<i>They should have warned you</i>

